  (!prop.exp ||
    (__BROWSER__ &&
      prop.exp.type === NodeTypes.SIMPLE_EXPRESSION &&
      !prop.exp.content.trim()))
) {
```

The condition handles:
1. `!prop.exp` - when there's no expression (non-browser case)
2. `__BROWSER__ && prop.exp.type === NodeTypes.SIMPLE_EXPRESSION && !prop.exp.content.trim()` - when the expression exists but is empty (browser case)

